## GitLab CLI (glab)

| Action | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Create/View/List/Close MR | `glab mr create/view/list/close <id>` |
| Project info | `glab repo view` |
| Pipeline status | `glab ci status` |

- **Always create MRs as drafts** — use `--draft` flag (do **not** also prefix the title with `Draft:` — the flag does that automatically)
- **Always enable "Delete source branch"** and **"Squash commits"** when creating MRs
- **MR description flag**: `glab mr create --description "..."` (NOT `--body` — that's `gh`)
- **CWD determines project** — `glab` resolves the target project from the git remote in CWD. `--repo` is unreliable. See project `CLAUDE.md` for CWD handling rules.
- **MR dependencies**: Open the dependency MR first, then the dependent MR. Set via: `glab api --method POST "projects/<project_id>/merge_requests/<iid>/blocks" -f "blocking_merge_request_id=<internal_mr_id>"` (use internal `id` from API, not `iid`)
